  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Provide 60000 Ugandan Children with Sport and Play</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Right To Play reaches over 63,000 children and youth, and plans to engage 71 schools and 39 community centres in Refugee camps in Uganda.  Additionally, 760 Leaders deliver sport and play programming - this enables children to experience the joy of play, but also helps them to build life skills such as leadership, discipline, fair play and conflict resolution.  Additionally, a focus on HIV/AIDS education, gender equality and child rights leads to healthier, happier and more peaceful communities.</narrative>
  </description>
